com.coveros.selenified

Class OutputFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.coveros.selenified.OutputFile

  • public class OutputFile
extends Object
    A custom output file, recording all details of every step performed, both actions and app. Actions, expected results, and actual results are captured. All asserts have a screenshot taken for traceability, while all failing actions also have a screenshot taken to assist with debugging purposes
    Version:
    3.0.3
    Author:
    Max Saperstone

                  String test,
                  Browser browser,
                  String url,
                  String suite,
                  String group,
                  String author,
                  String version,
                  String objectives)
        Creates a new instance of the OutputFile, which will serve as the detailed log
        Parameters:
        directory - - a string of the directory holding the files
        test - - a string value of the test name, typically the method name
        browser - - the browser the tests are running on
        url - - the url all of the tests are running against
        suite - - the test suite associated with the particular test
        group - - any testng groups associated with the particular test
        author - - the author associated with the particular test
        version - - the version of the test suite associated with the particular test
        objectives - - the test objectives, taken from the testng description

      • recordAction

        public void recordAction(String action,
                         String expectedResult,
                         String actualResult,
                         OutputFile.Result result)
        Writes an action that was performed out to the output file. If the action is considered a failure, and a 'real' browser is being used (not NONE or HTMLUNIT), then a screenshot will automatically be taken
        Parameters:
        action - - the step that was performed
        expectedResult - - the result that was expected to occur
        actualResult - - the result that actually occurred
        result - - the result of the action

      • recordActual

        public void recordActual(String actualOutcome,
                         OutputFile.Success result)
        Writes to the output file the actual outcome of an event. A screenshot is automatically taken to provide tracability for and proof of success or failure. This method should only be used after first writing the expected result, using the recordExpected method.
        Parameters:
        actualOutcome - - what the actual outcome was
        result - - whether this result is a pass or a failure

      • recordExpected

        public void recordExpected(String expectedOutcome)
        Writes to the output file the expected outcome of an event. This method should always be followed the recordActual method to record what actually happened.
        Parameters:
        expectedOutcome - - what the expected outcome is

      • finalizeOutputFile

        public void finalizeOutputFile()
        Ends and closes the output test file. The HTML is properly ended, and the file is analyzed to determine if the test passed or failed, and that information is updated, along with the overall timing of the test
